# ============================================================
# NAME:    ATAS (OrderFlowTrading / OFT.Platform)
# TYPE:    Program (order-flow trading platform)
# REPO:    https://github.com/kevshen13/surge-rules
# UPDATED: 2026-07-08
# DATA:    ATAS market data / order routing runs over CQG or Rithmic -> see cqg.list / rithmic.list.
# EXIT:    Put ATAS and its data source (CQG/Rithmic) on the SAME exit/region.
#          ATAS is the most sensitive to a program/data-source region mismatch (login fails + lag).
# NOTE:    LAN trading PCs proxy through Surge, so PROCESS-NAME does NOT apply to them;
#          the DOMAIN-SUFFIX rules below are what actually route ATAS app/license/update traffic.
#          DOMAIN-SUFFIX covers every sub-host (help./docs./updates./license./www. ...).
# ============================================================

# ---- ATAS app / license / update / site (suffix = all sub-hosts) ----
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,atas.net
DOMAIN-SUFFIX,orderflowtrading.net

# ---- Local-process hints (only effective if ATAS runs on the Surge host itself) ----
PROCESS-NAME,ATAS
PROCESS-NAME,ATAS X
PROCESS-NAME,ATASX
PROCESS-NAME,OFT.Platform

# ---- ADD NEW ATAS RULES BELOW ----
